%N A391166 Body-centered cubic pyritohedral numbers: a(n) = 1728*n^3 - 5076*n^2 + 4984*n - 1635.
%C A391166 These are figurate numbers produced in the construction of approximate pyritohedrons (dodecahedrons with irregular pentagonal faces) using points in a body-centered cubic lattice. The dihedral angle along the long edges for such a pyritohedron is 2*arctan(2) = A197376.
%C A391166 The n-th term is expressed as a summation which takes the (8*n-8)-th centered cube number (A005898) and adds 6 stacks - each layer the number of points. The stacks increase by 4 layers with unit increment in n, totaling 4*n-4 layers. This corresponds to constructing a pyritohedron by taking a cube and placing a wedge on each of its 6 faces.
%C A391166 So, a(n) = A005898(8*n-8) + 6*Sum_{i=2..n} (6*n+2*i-9)*(8*i-15) + (6*n+2*i-10)*(8*i-14) + (6*n+2*i-9)*(8*i-11) + (6*n+2*i-8)*(8*i-10).
